## Horsefly River Watershed Barrier Prioritization Summary {-}

The primary conservation outcome of the WCRP will be the remediation of barriers to connectivity in the Horsefly River watershed. To achieve Goal 1 in this plan, it is necessary to prioritize and identify a suite of barriers that, if remediated, will provide access to a minimum of 26.35 km of spawning or rearing habitat (@tbl-table16):




::: {#tbl-table16 .cell tbl-cap='Spawning and rearing habitat connectivity gain requirements to meet WCRP goals in the Horsefly River watershed. The measures of currently accessible and total habitat values are derived from the Intrinsic Potential habitat model described in Appendix B.' hash='appendixB_cache/pdf/tbl-table16_7d2a62dfc9ad8a8a041964e51ad3fd74'}
::: {.cell-output-display}
